# Micro:bit Smart Light

## Overview
This activity introduced students to basic IoT concepts using a microcontroller and a light sensor.

Students built a simple smart lighting system that reacts to changes in surrounding light.

## Target learners
- Ages 12–14

## Objective
- Understand sensors and outputs
- Learn basic coding logic
- Build confidence in electronics

# Materials
- BBC Micro:bit
- Light sensor
- LEDs
- Jumper wires
- Breadboard
- USB cable

# Learning Outcomes

Students were able to:
- understand how sensors detect changes
- use simple coding blocks
- test and troubleshoot their circuits
- apply logic to real-world problems

# Activity Flow

## Duration
2 hours
